{{nihongo|'''Keta Wakamiya Shrine'''|気多若宮神社|Keta Wakamiya Jinja}} is a [[Shinto]] [[Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in the city of [[Hida, Gifu|Hida]], [[Gifu Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is commonly referred to as "Sugimoto-sama" (杉本さま).

==History==
The original construction of this [[shrine]] is unknown, but it is said to have been constructed during the [[Heian period]]. [[Ōkuninushi]] and Kinomata-no-kami (木俣神) are the main gods of the shrine, but [[Amaterasu]] is also worshipped here.

==Recognition==
Keta Wakamiya Shrine is one of the shrines included in the Furukawa festival, which is one of the three main [[Hadaka Matsuri|naked festivals]] in Japan and is designated as an [[Intangible Cultural Properties of Japan]].

